  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d95\u0db1\u0dd1: \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0daf\u0da9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Laughter is required in public service: or fine",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Public servants who do not serve the people with a smile will be fined, said Aristotle Aguirre, the mayor of the city of Mulane, Philippines.",
        "The mayor pointed out that this decision was taken with the aim of improving the quality of public service by creating a friendly environment for the people who come to get the public service.",
        "People are frustrated with the public service. There are complaints from many residents who go to the public servants for their duties. Confidence in public service has been lost. Therefore, from now on, when public servants provide services to the people, they should do so with a smile. There is no room for complaints or complaints from the people. If such complaints are received, the relevant government officials will be punished. Public servants or officers who disregard this order will be subject to a maximum fine equal to 6 months' salary or suspension from work. Mayor Aristotle Aguirre has explained.",
        "Aristotle Aguirre has been mayor for 8 months. Even while running for the position of mayor, Aristotle Aguirre has resisted to create a quality public servant. Accordingly, considering the complaints from the people, he has introduced this 'smile policy'.",
        "Fishermen, agriculturists and people from remote areas come to the city for their work. They hustle for hours and days to get the job done. Complaints are received daily regarding the harassment of government employees. According to that, we should provide the kind of service that the people are satisfied with.''"
      ],
